parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Chain or Oil Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain or oil pump can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded in a dangerous location.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
often accompanied by warning lights or messages on the dashboard
such as "Low Oil Pressure" or "Drivetrain Malfunction". The engine may also make unusual noises or vibrate excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Timing Chain or Oil Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain or oil pump can cause catastrophic engine damage, resulting in expensive repairs or even requiring a new engine.
symptoms: The engine fails to start or runs rough
accompanied by unusual noises or vibrations. Warning lights or messages on the dashboard may indicate "Low Oil Pressure" or "Drivetrain Malfunction". In some cases
the vehicle may stall or shut down while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the timing chain breaks
the engine shuts down
the vehicle stalls
the drivetrain malfunction warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drivetrain malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drivetrain malfunction warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the vehicle stalls
the engine warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the u-joint can cause the driveshaft to break, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The u-joint fails
the driveshaft breaks
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Adaptive Headlight and Turn Signal Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of adaptive headlights, turn signals, daytime/parking lamps, and headlamp vehicle aim can cause reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and potentially dire situations for all involved.
symptoms: Inoperable front signals
requiring hand signals
which can be ineffective in certain environmental conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the passenger seat belt can cause the lock to fail to unlock, and the door to not open, potentially leading to entrapment in an emergency situation.
symptoms: Detail light reading "Driver Restraint Malfunction"
lock on the passenger seat belt failing to unlock
and the door not opening.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the engine can cause the vehicle to shut off, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: "Drivetrains Malfunction" warning
difficulty starting the engine
and low oil pressure warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door lock can cause the door to not lock or unlock properly, potentially leading to entrapment in an emergency situation.
symptoms: Door lock failing to lock or unlock
alarm sounding when trying to open the door
and slow or incomplete movement of the door lock pin.
